OL,3,CEx-minister helps Afghanistan inquiry
OL,4,Cbut says he 'won't betray'
OL,5,Cwhistleblowers
OL,7,FMr Mercer refused to budge, instead
OL,8,Fsaying he would "keep (his) word" to
OL,9,Fthose who confided in him.
OL,11,FThe ex-Conservative MP for Plymouth
OL,12,Fwas then given until 4pm on 25 July to
OL,13,Fhand over the names - or potentially
OL,14,Fface jail.
OL,16,FIn an update issued once the deadline
OL,17,Fhad passed, a spokesperson for the
OL,18,Finquiry said: "Mr Mercer has provided
OL,19,Ffurther information in response to the
OL,20,FSection 21 Notice and agreed to assist
OL,21,Fthe Inquiry further.
