OL,3,CEx-minister helps Afghanistan inquiry
OL,4,Cbut says he 'won't betray'
OL,5,Cwhistleblowers
OL,7,F"I will not betray those I served with
OL,8,Fwho have confided in me, whatever the
OL,9,Fcost.
OL,11,F"As I have repeatedly stated, it
OL,12,Fremains entirely inappropriate to name
OL,13,Fthose who confided in me without their
OL,14,Fconsent. For the avoidance of doubt: I
OL,15,Fhave not and I will not. I will always
OL,16,Fassist the Inquiry (outside of those
OL,17,Fparameters). This process has placed
OL,18,Fan unacceptable strain on me and my
OL,19,Ffamily. I am no longer a public
OL,20,Ffigure; I will not be commenting
OL,21,Ffurther."
